cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving the performance of Neural Machine Translation through data ordering techniques. The primary focus is on natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are covered under the Computer Science sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of pre-trained models and curriculum learning, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves the use of deep learning techniques for NLP tasks.
